# loom — project conventions

> Authoritative details: `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/adr/`.
> This file is a Cursor-mirror digest; when they disagree, the source docs win.

## Scope / session discipline

- Implement EXACTLY what was asked; do not expand scope (MCP / Skills / Plugins / harnesses)
  unless explicitly requested. When tempted to add infrastructure, first ask: "Did the user
  ask for this?" If unclear, ask before building.
- ≥3 independent steps or cross-many-calls work → maintain a task list, don't wing it.
- External SaaS / local-permission / third-party CLI tasks → run a 30s pre-flight
  (`which` / version / token-present / app-name-resolves), print pass/fail checklist.

## UI design pre-flight

Before writing any UI code (new component / modify existing / layout / interaction):
1. Quote verbatim the relevant design-doc section (file path + section anchor / line range).
   Don't infer. If you can't find it, stop and ask.
2. Declare component type: drawer / route / modal / page / other.
3. List files to be touched, marked create vs modify.
Skip for: pure docs / pure backend / pure schema / pure test / work inside an already-approved plan step.

## Stack (post YUK-321 M5)

- Hono API (`server/index.ts` + composition root `server/app.ts`, :8787)
- Vite SPA (`web/`, TanStack Router + React 19, :5173, dev `/api` proxy → :8787)
- pg-boss worker as separate process (`scripts/worker.ts`)
- Postgres + Drizzle (postgresql dialect, postgres driver); **no Redis**
- R2/S3 blob via `@aws-sdk/client-s3` (`src/server/r2.ts`)
- Claude Agent SDK via mimo Anthropic-compatible endpoint; self-hosted Node, NOT Vercel
- Switchable AI provider lane (YUK-365): default mimo-v2.5; `AI_PROVIDER_OVERRIDE=anthropic-sub`
  → Opus 4.8 via owner's Claude Max OAuth. **Token + override must be visible to ALL THREE
  processes** (API / Vite / worker). OAuth lane: set `CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN`, unset
  `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` / `_API_KEY` / `_AUTH_TOKEN` + 4 cloud-provider selectors.
  Wiring: `src/server/ai/providers.ts` + `runner.ts`.
- React 19, Tailwind v4 (CSS-first), Zustand, TanStack Query+Router, Zod, ts-fsrs
- Biome (lint+format), Vitest, pnpm, esbuild (`dist/{server,worker,migrate}.cjs`)

## Backend surface

Every route/job/copilotTool registers through capability manifests
(`src/capabilities/*/manifest.ts`) → composition root `server/app.ts`. There are NO
`app/api/**` Next.js route-handler shells anymore. Token check is middleware in
`server/app.ts` (`x-internal-token === INTERNAL_TOKEN`, exempt `/api/health`).
Browser code never holds the provider key — all AI calls funnel through Hono route or worker.

## Anti-patterns (this project)

- Destructive AI actions (delete question / merge node / reparent / archive) only `propose`;
  real mutation happens on user-accept route only.
- Don't expose profile-driven / manual-rescue / tool tasks via generic `/api/ai/[task]` —
  use domain routes or worker (only `ReviewIntentTask` uses the generic entry).
- Don't write derived lifecycle fields back to the source table — build a reader/projection.
- Don't refactor on a bug fix.
- Adding a new table/field requires a write path, or an allowlist entry in
  `scripts/audit-schema-allowlist.json` with a checkable `resolves_when`.

## Commands (cheat sheet)

```bash
pnpm dev:local       # compose Postgres :5433 + api + web + worker (推荐入口)
pnpm typecheck       # tsc --noEmit
pnpm lint            # biome check .
pnpm format          # biome format --write .
pnpm test:unit:watch # 快速无-DB watch
pnpm test:db:watch   # DB/API watch (Docker/OrbStack)
pnpm test            # full pre-PR gate: audit:profile + unit + db + migration-smoke
pnpm build           # rw:web:build + 三 esbuild 产物
```

Pre-PR: `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm audit:schema`,
`pnpm audit:partition`, `pnpm audit:profile`, `pnpm audit:draft-status`,
`pnpm test`, `pnpm build`.

## Conventions

- Toolchain: **Biome only** (no ESLint/Prettier) — 2-space / 100 col / single quotes /
  auto-organize imports; `noExplicitAny` + `useImportType` are warnings.
- TS strict + ESM + `@/*` → `src/*`.
- Issue tracker: **Linear** (`Yukoval Studios` / `YUK`). `YUK-XX` in PR titles / commit
  messages; branch `yuk-xx-...`. New work never uses bare `#N`.
- File mode: never hardcode `0o644` — respect umask (`0o666 & ~umask`).
- Respond in 中文 by default.
